1) TERMINAL GOT STUCK
I finished setting up my new virtual machine (Ubuntu) and when i did:

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

it updated my ubuntu, but my terminal seemed to be stuck, so i did:
pkill -9 gnome-terminal

2) CANT COPYPASTE FROM TERMINAL TO HOST AND VISE VERSA
i set up a new Ubuntu VM but i couldn't copypaste from VM to host machine and vise versa.
i checked the VM options and the clipboard was connected and shared. my VM was missing
open-vm-tools...
to check if i had it:

dpkg -l | grep open-vm-tools

- dpkg is a tool to install, build, remove and manage Debian packages
- -l is for listing
- | is piping
https://github.com/doll-exe/Linux/blob/main/bandit-over-the-wire/Piping%20and%20Redirection
i didn't have it so:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install open-vm-tools open-vm-tools-desktop -y
sudo reboot

3) /bin/sh ???
- is an executable file in the bin directory.
정확히는 sh의 확장판이 bash라고 보면 돼요. 보통 exploit 에서 타겟하는 것도 /bin/sh인 이유가 sh이 기본적으로 내장될 쉘이고, 
모든 컴퓨터에 존재하기 때문이에요. sh에 편의기능을 조금 더 추가한 것이 bash이고 이 외에도 zsh 같은 여러 쉘들이 있습니다.
